-- Czech Stocks: AAA Auto, CEZ, New World Resources Move in Prague
-- B y   K r y s t o f   C h a m o n i k o l a s
-- 2012-07-10T15:09:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-10/czech-stocks-aaa-auto-cez-new-world-resources-move-in-prague.html
The Czech Republic’s  PX (PX)  stock index
dropped 0.5 percent to 904.20 at the close in  Prague , a second
day of declines.  The following were among the most active  equities  in the
Czech market today. Stock symbols follow company names.  AAA Auto Group NV (AAA)   increased 0.6 percent, the most
in a week, to 18.34 koruna, after earlier rising as much as 2.5
percent. The chain of used-car dealerships in central and
eastern Europe said today it sold 16 percent more vehicles in
the first half of the year than in the same period of 2011.  CEZ AS (CEZ)   rose 1.1 percent to 713 koruna, rallying
for a third day, the longest run of gains in more than a month.
The biggest Czech power utility was raised to neutral from
underperform at Credit Suisse Group AG.  New World Resources Plc (NWR)  , the biggest Czech coking-
coal producer, retreated 1.4 percent to 103 koruna, a second day
of losses. Europe’s benchmark coal derivatives fell for a third
day, losing 0.3 percent to $96.75 koruna.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Krystof Chamonikolas in Prague at 
